   "body": "I have a log here from a run on a Neuropixels v2 probe (no motion correction) - everything seems to work as expected until the very last step\n\nIf this were any other step I'd mess with parameter options to try different things to get this to run without having to delve into the deeper code, but this doesn't seem to take any CLI arguments\n\nSeeking advice on how to handle from a high level (e.g., skip writing of certain columns, or filter out missing/None values) before moving on to the very low level (determining if the problem is with the capsule script, SpikeInterface, or NeuroConv itself)\n\nping @alejoe91 \ncc @yarikoptic \n\nLog file: [cea1981a-a13a-42e9-960f-27f4e9ecddfb.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/25471151/cea1981a-a13a-42e9-960f-27f4e9ecddfb.txt)\n",
